This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it focuses on deep latent variable models of natural language. Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of posterior inference and backpropagation, which are common issues in natural language processing. The paper also touches upon machine learning and neural networks, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
